      Executed DbCommand (2ms) [Parameters=[@__email_0='?'], CommandType='Text', CommandTimeout='30']
      SELECT u1.id, u1.created_at, u1.email, u1.failed_login_attempts, u1.first_name, u1.is_active, u1.last_login_at, u1.last_name, u1.password_changed_at, u1.locked_until, u1.pesel_masked, u1.password_hash, u1.phone, u1.require_password_change, u1.supervised_entity_id, u1.updated_at, s0.user_id, s0.role_id, s0.assigned_at, s0.id, s0.created_at, s0.description, s0.is_system_role, s0.name, s0.updated_at, s0.role_id0, s0.permission_id, s0.id0, s0.action, s0.description0, s0.name0, s0.resource
      FROM (
          SELECT u.id, u.created_at, u.email, u.failed_login_attempts, u.first_name, u.is_active, u.last_login_at, u.last_name, u.password_changed_at, u.locked_until, u.pesel_masked, u.password_hash, u.phone, u.require_password_change, u.supervised_entity_id, u.updated_at
          FROM users AS u
          WHERE u.email = @__email_0
          LIMIT 1
      ) AS u1
      LEFT JOIN (
          SELECT u0.user_id, u0.role_id, u0.assigned_at, r.id, r.created_at, r.description, r.is_system_role, r.name, r.updated_at, s.role_id AS role_id0, s.permission_id, s.id AS id0, s.action, s.description AS description0, s.name AS name0, s.resource
          FROM user_roles AS u0
          INNER JOIN roles AS r ON u0.role_id = r.id
          LEFT JOIN (
              SELECT r0.role_id, r0.permission_id, p.id, p.action, p.description, p.name, p.resource
              FROM role_permissions AS r0
              INNER JOIN permissions AS p ON r0.permission_id = p.id
          ) AS s ON r.id = s.role_id
      ) AS s0 ON u1.id = s0.user_id
      ORDER BY u1.id, s0.user_id, s0.role_id, s0.id, s0.role_id0, s0.permission_id

          SELECT u.id, u.created_at, u.email, u.failed_login_attempts, u.first_name, u.is_active, u.last_login_at, u.last_name, u.password_changed_at, u.locked_until, u.pesel_masked, u.password_hash, u.phone, u.require_password_change, u.supervised_entity_id, u.updated_at
          FROM users AS u
          WHERE u.email = @__email_0
          LIMIT 1
      ) AS u1
      LEFT JOIN (
          SELECT u0.user_id, u0.role_id, u0.assigned_at, r.id, r.created_at, r.description, r.is_system_role, r.name, r.updated_at, s.role_id AS role_id0, s.permission_id, s.id AS id0, s.action, s.description AS description0, s.name AS name0, s.resource
          FROM user_roles AS u0
          INNER JOIN roles AS r ON u0.role_id = r.id
          LEFT JOIN (
              SELECT r0.role_id, r0.permission_id, p.id, p.action, p.description, p.name, p.resource
              FROM role_permissions AS r0
              INNER JOIN permissions AS p ON r0.permission_id = p.id
          ) AS s ON r.id = s.role_id
      ) AS s0 ON u1.id = s0.user_id
      ORDER BY u1.id, s0.user_id, s0.role_id, s0.id, s0.role_id0, s0.permission_id

      FROM (
          SELECT u.id, u.created_at, u.email, u.failed_login_attempts, u.first_name, u.is_active, u.last_login_at, u.last_name, u.password_changed_at, u.locked_until, u.pesel_masked, u.password_hash, u.phone, u.require_password_change, u.supervised_entity_id, u.updated_at
          FROM users AS u
          WHERE u.email = @__email_0
          LIMIT 1
      ) AS u1
      LEFT JOIN (
          SELECT u0.user_id, u0.role_id, u0.assigned_at, r.id, r.created_at, r.description, r.is_system_role, r.name, r.updated_at, s.role_id AS role_id0, s.permission_id, s.id AS id0, s.action, s.description AS description0, s.name AS name0, s.resource
          FROM user_roles AS u0

      FROM (
          SELECT u.id, u.created_at, u.email, u.failed_login_attempts, u.first_name, u.is_active, u.last_login_at, u.last_name, u.password_changed_at, u.locked_until, u.pesel_masked, u.password_hash, u.phone, u.require_password_change, u.supervised_entity_id, u.updated_at
          FROM users AS u
          WHERE u.email = @__email_0
          LIMIT 1
      ) AS u1
      LEFT JOIN (
          SELECT u0.user_id, u0.role_id, u0.assigned_at, r.id, r.created_at, r.description, r.is_system_role, r.name, r.updated_at, s.role_id AS role_id0, s.permission_id, s.id AS id0, s.action, s.description AS description0, s.name AS name0, s.resource
          FROM user_roles AS u0
          INNER JOIN roles AS r ON u0.role_id = r.id
          LEFT JOIN (
              SELECT r0.role_id, r0.permission_id, p.id, p.action, p.description, p.name, p.resource
              FROM role_permissions AS r0
              INNER JOIN permissions AS p ON r0.permission_id = p.id
          ) AS s ON r.id = s.role_id
      ) AS s0 ON u1.id = s0.user_id
